{
  "texts": [
    "This patch generation agent is instructed to craft a patch in a specific format, and if the produced patch does not follow the format specification or cannot be applied to the original codebase, the agent enters a retry-loop which terminates after a pre-configured number of attempts.",
    "Finally, AutoCodeRover outputs a patch that attempts to resolve the original issue.We note that the workflow of AutoCodeRover discussed so far only requires the problem statement 𝑃 and codebase 𝐶 as input, and do not require any program specifications such as testcases.",
    "However, when testcases are available (e.g.",
    "provided by developers or generated from another tool), execution-based information and program analysis techniques can be integrated into the Au-toCodeRover framework (Section 4.4).",
    "For example, statistical fault localization [44] tool can be used to reveal more relevant methods beyond those mentioned in the problem statement."
  ]
}